Quote: <i>RHOMBOSOLEA PLEBEIA</i> (Richardson).  Sand-flounder; Patiki. One of the commonest flounders, frequenting deeper water than the yellow flounder, and never found in estuaries of rivers.
Notes: Phillipps Notes on the Edible Fishes

